1.	Use type instead of interface.
2.	Use const instead of let.
3.	Use const instead of var.
4.	Replace switch statements with if statements.
5.	Replace ternary operators with if statements.
6.	Use early return instead of else blocks.
7.	Use array methods (map, filter, reduce, etc.) instead of for loops.
8.	Use array methods or recursion instead of while loops.
9.	Use array methods or recursion instead of do-while loops.
10.	Use Object.keys(), Object.values(), or Object.entries() instead of for-in loops.
11.	Avoid using the delete operator. Instead, create a new object including only the desired properties.
12.	Do not mutate function parameters directly. Create and use new variables instead.
13.	Do not mutate properties of function parameters directly. Copy the object and work on the copy.
14.	Do not reassign function parameters. Use new variables instead.
